WEBVTT

00:03.373 --> 00:04.840
Previously on <i>Smash...</i>

00:04.875 --> 00:07.510
♪ Will come ♪

00:08.301 --> 00:10.402
- ♪ Whoo ♪
- All right, everyone,

00:10.436 --> 00:12.404
the incomparable
Rebecca Duvall.

00:12.438 --> 00:14.606
She's beautiful and famous,
and I wish I had her life.

00:14.641 --> 00:16.441
You're just in a good mood
because you have a date

00:16.476 --> 00:18.510
- with your chorus crush.
- So what do you want to do?

00:18.544 --> 00:19.745
When were you
going to tell me

00:19.779 --> 00:21.747
that that weasel
got press secretary?

00:21.781 --> 00:23.782
It's not exactly like we've
been on the same page lately.

00:23.816 --> 00:25.250
He's flunking two classes.

00:25.285 --> 00:26.785
This has kind of been
a tough time for me.

00:26.819 --> 00:28.687
The scene's
just getting started when...

00:28.721 --> 00:30.856
♪ I break into song ♪

00:30.890 --> 00:32.858
Her agent, her manager...
Everyone said she could sing.

00:32.892 --> 00:34.459
We hate her.

00:34.494 --> 00:35.761
♪ Yeah ♪

00:39.248 --> 00:41.300
Hey. I got your call.

00:41.334 --> 00:43.385
Karen, hi.
Thanks for coming in early.

00:43.419 --> 00:45.704
I usually
come in early anyway, so...

00:45.722 --> 00:50.208
Yeah. I know.

00:50.243 --> 00:53.929
Come with me.

00:53.980 --> 00:55.480
Is everything okay?

00:55.515 --> 00:56.648
Yeah, just wanted
to make sure you were

00:56.683 --> 00:58.150
staying on top
of the material.

00:58.184 --> 00:59.618
I know I haven't had
a chance

00:59.652 --> 01:01.219
to work with you on it yet.
Oh, no, I know.

01:01.254 --> 01:02.554
The stage manager
does that.

01:02.588 --> 01:04.056
What?

01:04.090 --> 01:05.390
That's what Linda
told me,

01:05.425 --> 01:07.259
that when we're through
with tech,

01:07.293 --> 01:09.328
she takes over the rehearsals
and works with the understudies

01:09.362 --> 01:11.596
so we're ready to go on
if we ever need to.

01:11.631 --> 01:15.467
Which I'm sure I won't.

01:15.501 --> 01:18.537
I think you'd make
a brilliant Marilyn.

01:20.673 --> 01:23.608
I see it, you know?

01:23.643 --> 01:26.511
In my head.

01:26.546 --> 01:29.514
Really?

01:29.549 --> 01:31.817
Mmhmm.

01:36.622 --> 01:38.357
[Sighs]
Okay, just, um,

01:38.391 --> 01:40.525
stay on top
of the material.

01:47.066 --> 01:48.467
Oh, my God.

01:48.501 --> 01:50.702
She's coming
straight from the gym.

01:50.737 --> 01:53.338
Randall, hey. Can I talk
to you for a second?

01:53.373 --> 01:55.674
- No, actually.
- I'm not kidding.

01:55.708 --> 01:58.610
She's going to be
at least 20 minutes late.

01:58.644 --> 02:01.313
You should go tell one
of the stage management people.

02:01.347 --> 02:02.881
Thank you.

02:02.915 --> 02:04.816
[Sighs]

02:04.851 --> 02:07.486
Yes?

02:07.520 --> 02:10.455
I just heard something I think
your boss needs to know.

02:10.490 --> 02:12.657
[Upbeat piano intro]

02:12.692 --> 02:15.727
♪ See the girl
who's become a joke ♪

02:15.762 --> 02:18.980
♪ See the man
whose heart she broke ♪

02:19.015 --> 02:22.150
♪ Right here ♪

02:22.185 --> 02:26.738
♪ On Lexington
and 52nd street ♪

02:26.773 --> 02:28.573
Sounds great, Ted.

02:28.608 --> 02:30.975
Anything else you want
to brush up, Derek?

02:30.993 --> 02:32.711
How late is she
gonna be again?

02:32.745 --> 02:35.080
What? No, I'm not late.
I'm here. Sorry.

02:35.114 --> 02:37.032
Huh. Terrific.

02:37.083 --> 02:38.717
We're gonna look
at <i>Mr. & Mrs. Smith.</i>

02:38.751 --> 02:42.020
Oh, um, can we start
with something else?

02:42.055 --> 02:43.388
No. It's on the schedule.

02:43.423 --> 02:46.374
Uh, Derek...

02:46.426 --> 02:48.560
Um...

02:48.594 --> 02:50.679
Ahh.

02:50.713 --> 02:52.597
I've had this great idea
about <i>Mr. & Mrs. Smith,</i>

02:52.632 --> 02:54.933
which I need to talk
to Julia about,

02:54.967 --> 02:57.169
'cause it requires a little
rewrite, takes a little time.

02:57.203 --> 02:59.738
So, um,
could we focus on...

02:59.772 --> 03:01.573
I've done a lot of work
on <i>Wolf.</i>

03:01.607 --> 03:04.743
[Clears throat]
Give me a minute.

03:06.546 --> 03:08.346
They are not going to cut
<i>Mr. & Mrs. Smith.</i>

03:08.381 --> 03:10.732
Yeah, well, I heard her.
That's what she told them.

03:10.783 --> 03:12.751
She wants to cut it
and replace it with a scene.

03:12.785 --> 03:14.920
- Ugh, she's a nightmare.
- I like her.

03:14.954 --> 03:16.354
You like everybody.

03:16.389 --> 03:17.856
Excuse me,
I do not like everybody,

03:17.874 --> 03:19.591
but I do like Rebecca.
She's very direct.

03:19.625 --> 03:21.359
Okay, thanks, bye.

03:21.394 --> 03:25.564
Hey, Karen!

03:25.598 --> 03:26.898
Rebecca, hey.

03:26.933 --> 03:28.800
What are you doing tonight?

03:28.835 --> 03:30.702
- Um...
- Want to go out?

03:30.720 --> 03:31.937
Sure, yeah.

03:31.971 --> 03:35.107
- Great. Call you.
- Okay.

03:37.260 --> 03:38.677
What just happened?

03:44.734 --> 03:46.067
I hate her.

03:46.102 --> 03:47.919
Would you please
close the door?

03:47.954 --> 03:51.490
You don't replace songs
with scenes.

03:51.524 --> 03:52.824
I didn't say I would.

03:52.859 --> 03:54.826
You didn't say you wouldn't.

03:54.861 --> 03:57.095
There's a lot of ways
to build a musical, Tom.

03:57.130 --> 03:59.464
Like bringing in
outside songwriters?

03:59.499 --> 04:01.133
- Let's not go back to that.
- It was hardly out of line.

04:01.167 --> 04:02.734
It happens all the time.

04:02.768 --> 04:05.103
People cave in to actresses
all the time too.

04:05.138 --> 04:06.505
- Meaning?
- You're the director.

04:06.539 --> 04:09.474
Why don't you...
Oh, what is the word...

04:09.509 --> 04:10.976
Direct?

04:11.010 --> 04:12.511
[Chuckles]

04:12.545 --> 04:13.979
[Door opens]

04:14.013 --> 04:15.947
[Keyboard clicking]

04:15.982 --> 04:18.450
Oh, Julia, you have a message.
Leo called.

04:18.483 --> 04:20.819
He said he's staying with your
husband an extra night.

04:20.853 --> 04:23.254
Great.
Now I have to take messages

04:23.272 --> 04:26.258
about my broken marriage
from him.

04:26.292 --> 04:28.593
[Sighs]

04:28.628 --> 04:31.830
- Hey. You're home.
- Where should I be?

04:31.864 --> 04:33.148
- No, it's just
it's not even 6:00.

04:33.182 --> 04:34.432
You're never home
this early.

04:34.467 --> 04:36.168
Wait. Did you get fired?

04:36.202 --> 04:39.137
No. He's not going
to fire me.

04:39.172 --> 04:42.641
It's too much fun to keep me
around and torture me.

04:42.675 --> 04:45.327
- Aw, maybe you should quit.
- Why should I?

04:45.378 --> 04:47.012
If they want to pay me
to sit around and do nothing

04:47.046 --> 04:49.481
apart from come home early
and take my girlfriend

04:49.515 --> 04:50.832
out for dinner,
I'm gonna let them.

04:50.867 --> 04:54.386
Oh. I have a date.

04:54.420 --> 04:56.054
With a movie star.

04:56.088 --> 04:58.023
[Squeals]
I have a date with a movie star.

04:58.057 --> 04:59.658
- Oh.
- It's kinda cool, right?

04:59.692 --> 05:01.960
I mean, it's kinda cool.

05:01.994 --> 05:04.029
- Mm.
- Oh, I have a date!

05:04.063 --> 05:05.530
Whee!

05:05.565 --> 05:08.366
Hey, Rebecca,
smile right here!

05:08.401 --> 05:11.002
[Camera lenses clicking]
Rebecca, would you turn around?

05:11.037 --> 05:14.673
Miss Duvall!
Oh, looking good, miss Duvall.

05:17.827 --> 05:20.378
- Who's playing tonight?
- Cooper's about to do a set.

05:20.413 --> 05:21.913
- Oh, great.
- Cooper?

05:21.948 --> 05:23.648
They're fantastic.
I love them.

05:23.683 --> 05:25.684
Yeah? You want to stand in?

05:25.718 --> 05:27.252
What?

05:27.286 --> 05:29.020
You're supposed to be
Derek's muse.

05:29.055 --> 05:30.322
I want to see what you got.

05:30.356 --> 05:31.990
Who told you that?

05:32.008 --> 05:34.158
People talk.
They say you're brilliant.

05:34.176 --> 05:35.493
Come on.
Oh.

05:35.511 --> 05:37.545
It'll be fun.
Come on.

05:37.597 --> 05:41.199
Hey, Paulie.
Hey, Phil. Hi.

05:41.234 --> 05:43.334
- How's it going?
- Good, good.

05:43.352 --> 05:45.220
This is my friend
Karen Cartwright.

05:45.271 --> 05:47.005
Be kind.

05:47.039 --> 05:49.274
All right.

05:49.308 --> 05:52.027
Hey, everyone, listen up.

05:52.061 --> 05:56.248
Karen Cartwright.
Give it up.

05:56.282 --> 05:57.949
What about...<i>Run?</i>

05:57.984 --> 05:59.284
- Snow patrol.
- Yeah.

05:59.318 --> 06:00.619
What are you up to?

06:00.653 --> 06:03.555
I'm just checking out
the competition.

06:09.595 --> 06:15.433
♪ I'll sing it
one last time for you ♪

06:15.468 --> 06:20.772
♪ Then we really
have to go ♪

06:20.806 --> 06:26.544
♪ You've been the only thing
that's right ♪

06:26.579 --> 06:30.598
♪ In all I've done ♪

06:33.986 --> 06:37.155
♪ Light up, light up ♪

06:37.189 --> 06:41.626
♪ As if you have
a choice ♪

06:41.661 --> 06:47.282
♪ Even if you cannot hear
my voice ♪

06:47.333 --> 06:52.871
♪ I'll be right
beside you, dear ♪

07:00.479 --> 07:06.318
♪ To think I might not see
those eyes ♪

07:06.352 --> 07:11.823
♪ Makes it so hard
not to cry ♪

07:11.857 --> 07:16.828
♪ And as we say
our long good-byes ♪

07:16.862 --> 07:20.498
♪ I nearly do ♪

07:25.237 --> 07:28.323
♪ Light up, light up ♪

07:28.374 --> 07:32.544
♪ As if you have
a choice ♪

07:32.578 --> 07:38.116
♪ Even if you cannot hear
my voice ♪

07:38.134 --> 07:44.956
♪ I'll be right
beside you, dear ♪

07:44.974 --> 07:50.962
♪ Oh, oh ♪

07:50.996 --> 07:56.634
♪ Oh, oh ♪

07:56.669 --> 07:58.669
♪ Oh, oh, oh ♪

08:02.942 --> 08:04.942
♪ Oh, oh, oh ♪

08:09.415 --> 08:13.218
♪ Light up, light up ♪

08:13.252 --> 08:17.722
♪ As if you have a choice ♪

08:17.757 --> 08:23.395
♪ Even if you cannot hear
my voice ♪

08:23.429 --> 08:28.299
♪ I'll be right
beside you, dear ♪

08:30.936 --> 08:32.386
[Cheers and applause]

08:32.438 --> 08:34.005
Whoo!

08:34.023 --> 08:36.558
Thanks. Thank you.
That was so awesome.

08:36.609 --> 08:39.477
Thank you.

08:43.732 --> 08:46.401
You are not an understudy.
You are a star.

08:46.452 --> 08:48.219
Oh!

08:48.254 --> 08:51.239
[Orchestra tuning up]

08:52.025 --> 08:54.125
SMASH
S01 Ep12 - Publicity

08:54.754 --> 08:58.254
Sync and corrected by dr.jackson
for www.addic7ed.com

09:06.574 --> 09:08.826
- Hello. What's that?
- Nothing.

09:09.811 --> 09:11.812
Hm, yeah. Really.

09:11.846 --> 09:13.480
Seriously, it's...
It's not anything.

09:13.514 --> 09:15.350
[Chuckles]

09:16.684 --> 09:19.686
Unless you want
to talk about it.

09:22.666 --> 09:24.167
What are we gonna do
when she can't sing it?

09:24.201 --> 09:25.568
Because I am not cutting it.

09:25.602 --> 09:27.086
We haven't even
heard it yet.

09:27.121 --> 09:30.640
I'm telling you,
she cannot sing it.

09:30.674 --> 09:32.342
And you have lost control
of the rehearsal room!

09:32.376 --> 09:36.913
The only person who has clearly
lost control, Tom, is you!

09:36.947 --> 09:39.515
Tom, Derek.
The company is waiting.

09:39.550 --> 09:41.517
Right outside the door.

09:41.552 --> 09:45.221
Well, let them in.
We have work to do.

09:47.000 --> 09:53.074
