contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

10:02.139 --> 10:03.606
[Sighs]
Well.

10:03.624 --> 10:04.874
[Clears throat]

10:04.908 --> 10:06.776
What should we start with?

10:06.794 --> 10:08.711
Actually, Tom and Julia
have written a new number.

10:08.746 --> 10:11.781
It's a ballad
entitled <i>Secondhand...</i>

10:11.799 --> 10:13.182
<i>Secondhand</i>
<i>white baby grand.</i>

10:13.217 --> 10:14.717
Oh, really?

10:14.752 --> 10:16.052
It's about Marilyn
and her mother,

10:16.086 --> 10:18.471
how she felt unwanted
as a child.

10:18.505 --> 10:20.857
Oh, is it any good, Tom?

10:20.891 --> 10:25.895
It's not actually
for you, darling... sorry.

10:25.929 --> 10:27.397
We're going to give it
to Marilyn's shadow selves...

10:27.431 --> 10:29.165
You know,
the voices in her head.

10:29.199 --> 10:32.335
Thought they could take on
some of the more internal songs.

10:32.369 --> 10:34.404
Shadow selves.

10:34.438 --> 10:37.006
Derek, maybe you and Rebecca
and I could have a sidebar.

10:37.040 --> 10:39.242
[Laughs] I don't need
a sidebar, Randall.

10:39.276 --> 10:42.044
I think that's
a really interesting idea.

10:42.079 --> 10:44.213
But you know
who should sing it?

10:44.248 --> 10:48.017
Karen.

10:48.051 --> 10:51.421
She's got
a real rock star voice.

10:51.455 --> 10:53.589
Thank you, Rebecca.

10:53.624 --> 10:56.626
She does indeed.

10:59.463 --> 11:01.397
Thank you.

11:04.134 --> 11:05.518
Aah!
[Laughs]

11:05.552 --> 11:07.904
What is all this?

11:07.938 --> 11:10.039
I did a campaign
for Molly m last month.

11:10.073 --> 11:11.441
I thought maybe you
could use some of it.

11:11.475 --> 11:12.725
Look.

11:12.776 --> 11:15.011
This is a $2,000 jacket.

11:15.045 --> 11:16.379
I know.

11:16.413 --> 11:17.713
They gave me so much stuff,

11:17.748 --> 11:19.382
I don't know
what to do with it.

11:19.416 --> 11:20.867
Seriously, you'd be doing me
a favor; Take it.

11:20.901 --> 11:23.069
You can't live your life
in yoga gear.

11:23.120 --> 11:24.353
I'd never get away
with it.

11:24.371 --> 11:26.956
Oh, yeah,
but you're you.

11:26.990 --> 11:30.793
Yeah.
Don't you want to be me.

11:30.828 --> 11:33.863
Wow. Who's that?

11:33.897 --> 11:37.467
- Oh, that's my boyfriend, Dev.
- Boyfriend?

11:37.501 --> 11:39.268
You live together.

11:39.303 --> 11:41.137
- Yeah.
- Hmm.

11:41.171 --> 11:43.372
Well, take it from me.

11:43.407 --> 11:45.575
Boyfriends can be a problem
on the way up.

11:45.609 --> 11:47.743
Oh, Dev's not a problem.

11:47.778 --> 11:49.045
Hmm.

11:49.079 --> 11:51.147
He might be.

11:51.181 --> 11:54.417
♪ And I ♪

11:54.451 --> 11:58.154
♪ I walk dead on line ♪

11:58.188 --> 12:02.592
[Electric guitar intro]

12:02.626 --> 12:06.579
[Dance beat]

12:06.613 --> 12:08.998
♪ And I ♪

12:09.032 --> 12:12.468
♪ I walk dead on line ♪

12:12.503 --> 12:13.836
[Footsteps approach]

12:13.871 --> 12:15.671
Oh. You're up.

12:15.706 --> 12:17.273
I texted you.

12:17.307 --> 12:19.342
Rebecca wanted to go to
this new restaurant, Dev,

12:19.376 --> 12:20.626
and we had
such a great time.

12:20.677 --> 12:21.928
Leonardo diCaprio was there,

12:21.962 --> 12:23.613
and then David Bowie
showed up.

12:23.647 --> 12:24.947
He's totally nice.

12:24.982 --> 12:26.582
Did he join you
for tequila shots

12:26.617 --> 12:27.850
in the meatpacking district?

12:27.885 --> 12:29.452
[Giggles]

12:29.486 --> 12:31.187
24hour news cycle.

12:31.221 --> 12:33.456
You and your new girlfriend
are everywhere.

12:33.490 --> 12:36.526
- They follow her around.
- Yeah, and you too, apparently.

12:36.560 --> 12:37.960
Wait, are you mad?

12:37.995 --> 12:40.463
No, I'm just confused.

12:40.497 --> 12:42.999
Why? It's fantastic.
It's exciting.

12:43.033 --> 12:44.867
Okay, but did you buy
all this stuff?

12:44.902 --> 12:46.285
I mean, it must have cost
a bloody fortune.

12:46.320 --> 12:47.603
Rebecca gave it to me.

12:47.638 --> 12:49.956
They give her clothes
for free.

12:49.990 --> 12:51.140
- Yeah.
- I mean, they...

12:51.174 --> 12:52.174
They do this for movie stars.

12:52.209 --> 12:53.476
You know this.

12:53.510 --> 12:54.844
No, I didn't, actually.

12:54.878 --> 12:56.178
But, uh, I do now.
I'm learning.

12:56.213 --> 12:58.047
As are you, apparently.

12:58.081 --> 13:00.783
You'll like her.
She's so much fun.

13:00.801 --> 13:03.619
This is cool, Dev.

13:03.654 --> 13:06.355
This is cool.
[Soft piano music]

13:06.390 --> 13:08.791
"It is who you are
in your deepest soul

13:08.825 --> 13:11.477
that will make you
a great actress."

13:11.511 --> 13:14.063
Lights up
on shadow self 1.

13:14.097 --> 13:16.165
"Mama bought the piano."

13:16.199 --> 13:18.568
Shadow self 2.

13:18.602 --> 13:20.636
"Then mama went away."

13:20.654 --> 13:22.805
"Remember your childhood."

13:22.839 --> 13:25.524
Shadow self 3.

13:25.576 --> 13:29.312
♪ My mother
bought it secondhand ♪

13:29.346 --> 13:33.015
♪ From a silent movie star ♪

13:33.050 --> 13:35.651
♪ It was out of tune ♪

13:35.686 --> 13:39.422
♪ But still I learned
to play ♪

13:39.456 --> 13:41.257
Karen's going to sound
so great on this.

13:41.291 --> 13:42.508
[Door opens]

13:42.542 --> 13:45.094
- Leo?
- No. It's me.

13:45.128 --> 13:47.513
Hey, Tom.
Frank.

13:47.547 --> 13:49.865
- I was just going.
- No, no.

13:49.900 --> 13:51.500
You're working.
I don't want to interrupt.

13:51.535 --> 13:53.402
I'm just here
to pick up Leo.

13:53.437 --> 13:55.371
You can't pick Leo up.
Leo's with you.

13:55.405 --> 13:56.672
He already left?

13:56.707 --> 13:57.907
What do you mean,
he already left?

13:57.941 --> 13:59.442
He never came home.

13:59.476 --> 14:00.743
He's been with you
for the last two days.

14:00.777 --> 14:02.612
No, he hasn't.

14:02.646 --> 14:03.879
What do you mean,
no he hasn't?

14:03.914 --> 14:06.349
Yesterday I got a message
saying...

14:06.383 --> 14:09.218
Julia, I got a message
the day before.

14:09.252 --> 14:12.421
He texted me
he was staying with you.

14:12.456 --> 14:15.925
When was the last time
you saw him?

14:28.265 --> 14:30.865
So, who was the last who seen him?

14:32.116 --> 14:35.535
He was in school
on Monday.

14:35.569 --> 14:38.705
Um, his last class
gets out at 3:30.

14:38.739 --> 14:41.841
It's, uh, advanced placement
American history.

14:41.876 --> 14:43.710
- Smart kid?
- Yes.

14:43.744 --> 14:46.079
[Sniffs]
And he works hard.

14:46.113 --> 14:49.182
He's never screwing around.
He's always doing his homework.

14:49.216 --> 14:52.252
Sort of a serious kid.

14:52.286 --> 14:55.788
Very tender-hearted.

14:55.823 --> 14:57.557
He's younger than he looks.

14:57.591 --> 15:00.627
He was arrested a few months
ago for smoking pot

15:00.661 --> 15:01.961
in Central Park.

15:01.996 --> 15:03.463
Oh, so he's got a record.

15:03.497 --> 15:06.633
No, it was dismissed.

15:06.667 --> 15:08.101
I'm not gonna lie
to you.

15:08.135 --> 15:10.570
Running away is
about the most dangerous thing

15:10.604 --> 15:13.239
a kid can do in New York.

15:13.274 --> 15:16.876
Trouble at home?

15:16.911 --> 15:19.279
They're building sets
in Boston.

15:19.313 --> 15:22.315
And you have
movie star problems.

15:25.352 --> 15:26.753
Tom and Sam
were talking about it.

15:26.787 --> 15:30.089
But everybody's
talking about it.

15:30.124 --> 15:31.758
People start whispering
about who's in charge

15:31.792 --> 15:33.826
because nobody knows.

15:33.861 --> 15:37.597
This is what happens
when a show starts to go down.

15:37.631 --> 15:38.998
What did they say?

15:39.033 --> 15:41.134
They can issue
a missing persons report.

15:41.168 --> 15:44.904
They'll canvass the train
station and the airport.

15:44.939 --> 15:47.974
We have to go to his school,
talk to his friends.

15:48.008 --> 15:50.143
It's been two days.
He could be anywhere.

15:50.177 --> 15:52.278
What do you need?

15:52.313 --> 15:53.846
Just don't tell anyone.

15:53.881 --> 15:56.582
I need to not have
Eileen and Derek flipping out

15:56.600 --> 15:58.017
while I deal with this.

15:58.052 --> 15:59.819
How is Frank?

15:59.853 --> 16:03.189
[Sighs]
We're both exhausted.

16:05.059 --> 16:07.493
Where's Marilyn?

16:07.528 --> 16:09.195
Where's stage management?

16:09.229 --> 16:10.997
Oh, they ran out
to the hall.

16:11.031 --> 16:13.666
Rebecca was teaching her how
to make one of her smoothies.

16:13.701 --> 16:16.402
Smoothies.

16:25.379 --> 16:27.013
[Laughing]

16:27.047 --> 16:29.182
This is a piece of junk,
but what are you gonna do?

16:29.216 --> 16:33.169
So the kale goes in...

16:33.220 --> 16:34.721
With the coconut milk.

16:34.755 --> 16:36.723
Don't you have
an assistant for this?

16:36.757 --> 16:38.558
I have an assistant
and a manager,

16:38.592 --> 16:40.560
but they're both working
their asses off right now,

16:40.594 --> 16:42.128
trying to find me a decent place
to live in Boston

16:42.162 --> 16:43.663
for eight weeks.

16:43.697 --> 16:45.398
Yeah, well,
Linda has production duties.

16:45.432 --> 16:46.966
We're almost done.

16:47.001 --> 16:49.836
Um, actually, it's best
to grind the flaxseed

16:49.870 --> 16:51.471
and then throw it in,

16:51.505 --> 16:52.872
but we don't seem to have
a spice mill,

16:52.906 --> 16:55.675
so what are you gonna do?

16:55.709 --> 16:57.310
It'll just take three minutes.

16:57.344 --> 17:00.046
Give me that.

17:00.080 --> 17:01.314
- Rebecca.
- Mm hmm?

17:01.348 --> 17:02.682
I start teching
in a week.

17:02.716 --> 17:06.035
I don't have three minutes.

17:06.086 --> 17:09.689
Um, well, uh,
if you could just do it all,

17:09.723 --> 17:10.990
and, um,
and then bring it in,

17:11.025 --> 17:12.224
that would be great.

17:12.259 --> 17:15.127
Thanks.

17:18.565 --> 17:20.683
I will not have
my stage manager hijacked

17:20.718 --> 17:22.385
to make smoothies.

17:22.419 --> 17:25.003
Especially if we have to rewrite
half the show

17:25.039 --> 17:27.040
just so she can do it.

17:27.074 --> 17:28.374
- What do you want me to say?
- I want you to say,

17:28.409 --> 17:30.009
"Derek, you are in charge,

17:30.044 --> 17:32.578
"and I will speak to our star
and tell her how to behave."

17:32.613 --> 17:35.347
- I did that last week.
- Do it again.

17:35.365 --> 17:38.735
How's the new song?

17:38.786 --> 17:41.888
Karen's learning it.
We'll start staging it tomorrow.

17:41.922 --> 17:43.756
Which is exactly when
I want to hear from you

17:43.791 --> 17:46.709
about what you're going to do
to alleviate this situation.

17:46.744 --> 17:48.728
This one.

17:48.762 --> 17:50.696
Don't leave this till
we're teching next week.

17:50.731 --> 17:53.032
I called Bam
and added your plus-one.

17:53.067 --> 17:54.300
Thank you.

17:54.334 --> 17:56.035
Yeah, they were a little bit
confused

17:56.070 --> 17:57.770
because apparently
Jerry's going to be there too.

17:57.805 --> 17:59.872
Just thought you'd like
a heads-up.

17:59.907 --> 18:03.776
Ellis, there's something
I need you to do.

18:10.918 --> 18:12.652
Hey.

18:12.686 --> 18:14.253
Ellis, what's all this?

18:14.288 --> 18:15.788
A vitamix, a grain mill,
and a spice mill

18:15.823 --> 18:17.890
for grinding flaxseed.

18:17.925 --> 18:20.159
Oh, they put you
in charge of smoothies.

18:20.194 --> 18:22.095
- Yes, they did.
- Hm.

18:22.129 --> 18:23.963
Show biz.

18:23.997 --> 18:26.799
♪ My mother bought it
secondhand ♪

18:26.834 --> 18:30.903
♪ From a silent movie star ♪

18:30.938 --> 18:32.939
♪ It was out of tune ♪

18:32.973 --> 18:38.144
♪ But still I learned
to play ♪

18:38.178 --> 18:40.446
♪ And with each note ♪

18:40.481 --> 18:42.782
♪ We both would smile ♪

18:42.816 --> 18:44.283
She sounds pretty good.

18:44.318 --> 18:47.487
Yes, she does.

18:47.521 --> 18:48.988
But you should have
that song.

18:49.022 --> 18:52.358
I'm well aware.

18:56.697 --> 18:58.965
Tom, the song is gorgeous.

18:58.999 --> 19:01.334
And this one sounds
sensational on it.

19:01.368 --> 19:03.136
- Thanks.
- Were you waiting for me?

19:03.170 --> 19:05.505
Oh, yeah. Sam said you guys
were meeting up for a drink.

19:05.539 --> 19:06.806
I wanted to come along.

19:06.840 --> 19:08.207
Let me get my stuff.

19:08.242 --> 19:10.343
- Do you want to come?
- I can't.

19:10.377 --> 19:11.994
I'm having dinner
with Rebecca and Dev.

19:12.045 --> 19:13.813
- I wanted her to meet him.
- Wow.

19:13.847 --> 19:17.950
That's bold, since you're dating
both of them.

19:17.985 --> 19:19.635
Kidding, kidding.

19:19.670 --> 19:21.888
Funny. It's so weird
that they write that stuff.

19:21.922 --> 19:23.673
I mean, in Iowa,
people think that's real.

19:23.724 --> 19:26.492
My parents called three times
to find out if I was a lesbian.

19:26.527 --> 19:30.062
They better get used to it.
You're on your way.

19:30.097 --> 19:31.497
And so am I.

19:31.532 --> 19:33.683
- See ya.
- Good work.

19:33.734 --> 19:36.035
Thanks.

19:43.193 --> 19:46.593
We actualy don't hang on anymore.

19:48.549 --> 19:51.017
If you don't hang out
with him any more,

19:51.051 --> 19:52.585
who does?

19:52.619 --> 19:54.887
I don't know.
He's into, like, wrestling now.

19:54.922 --> 19:56.422
Yes, we're aware.

19:56.457 --> 19:59.692
Have you talked
to the wrestling coach?

19:59.726 --> 20:02.028
Yes, actually,
we did talk to him,

20:02.062 --> 20:03.529
as well as some kids
on the team

20:03.564 --> 20:05.832
who said that we should talk
to you, Mason,

20:05.866 --> 20:07.366
because you're his best friend.

20:07.401 --> 20:08.768
I don't know.

20:08.802 --> 20:11.804
Maybe the police could help.

20:17.478 --> 20:19.362
It is so hard,
what you're going through.

20:19.396 --> 20:20.947
I can't even imagine.

20:20.981 --> 20:24.083
- Well, if you hear anything...
- Oh, absolutely.

20:35.045 --> 20:37.463
So this is how
the other half lives.

20:37.498 --> 20:41.083
Once in a while.

20:41.134 --> 20:44.103
[Majestic music]

20:44.137 --> 20:45.471
♪ ♪

20:45.506 --> 20:48.474
[East Indian music]

20:48.509 --> 20:50.059
♪ ♪

20:50.093 --> 20:52.711
Oh, here she is, babe.
Here she is.

20:52.729 --> 20:54.397
Yay.

20:54.431 --> 20:56.549
You didn't have a hard time
finding it, did you?

20:56.567 --> 20:58.818
No, not at all.

20:58.852 --> 21:01.921
345.
The address is the name.

21:01.955 --> 21:04.590
Hi. Rebecca.

21:04.625 --> 21:06.609
I know who you are.
Dev. Dev Sundaram.

21:06.660 --> 21:08.894
Nice to meet you finally.

21:08.912 --> 21:10.663
Uh, is this tap?

21:10.697 --> 21:14.133
I actually need something
bottled... flat, not sparkling.

21:14.167 --> 21:16.469
It doesn't have to be
mineral water,

21:16.503 --> 21:17.920
just something in a bottle.

21:17.955 --> 21:20.106
- Fiji okay?
- Yes, thank you.

21:20.140 --> 21:23.509
- Mm-hmm.
- Great.

21:23.544 --> 21:25.094
Indian.

21:25.128 --> 21:26.679
Sorry?

21:26.713 --> 21:29.515
345. I never expected
that to be

21:29.550 --> 21:31.617
an Indian restaurant.

21:31.652 --> 21:32.919
- Oh, I'm sorry.
- Oh, no.

21:32.953 --> 21:34.353
Do you not eat Indian food?

21:34.388 --> 21:36.489
I have a peanut allergy.

21:36.523 --> 21:38.124
- Oh, then you're fine.
- No.

21:38.158 --> 21:40.092
It's a real allergy,
not a pretend allergy.

21:40.110 --> 21:41.494
No, you're still fine.

21:41.528 --> 21:43.029
There are no peanuts
in Indian cooking.

21:43.063 --> 21:44.463
Not even in curry?

21:44.498 --> 21:46.132
Well, that's Thai.

21:46.166 --> 21:49.635
[Fake Indian accent] There's no
such thing as an Indian curry?

21:49.670 --> 21:51.837
There is such a thing
as an... an Indian curry,

21:51.872 --> 21:53.339
but there are no peanuts
in it.

21:53.373 --> 21:55.157
Some northern Indian dishes
sometimes...

21:55.208 --> 21:57.877
- Ah.
- But this is South Indian.

21:57.911 --> 21:59.879
We can go to another
restaurant if you want.

21:59.913 --> 22:01.447
No, no. No.

22:01.465 --> 22:03.833
I like it.
It's charming. It's cute.

22:03.884 --> 22:06.018
I love Bollywood.

22:06.053 --> 22:07.987
Um...

22:08.021 --> 22:12.892
Do you have something
without peanuts in it?

22:12.926 --> 22:15.161
The stillness they achieve,
it seems like

22:15.195 --> 22:16.529
nothing's happening at all,

22:16.563 --> 22:18.898
and yet it's
completely mesmerizing.

22:18.932 --> 22:20.983
Wow.
You guys really like it.

22:21.018 --> 22:22.335
You didn't?

22:22.369 --> 22:24.170
I guess maybe I don't
understand art.

22:24.204 --> 22:25.504
Actually, you don't have
to understand it.

22:25.539 --> 22:27.073
You just respond to it.

22:27.107 --> 22:28.341
How does it make you feel?

22:28.375 --> 22:29.675
It made me feel
pretty bored.

22:29.710 --> 22:31.911
Oh.
[Chuckles]

22:31.945 --> 22:33.412
This is a merry crew.

22:33.447 --> 22:34.830
Nina.

22:34.865 --> 22:36.215
Ben.

22:36.249 --> 22:38.050
Jerry.

22:38.085 --> 22:40.536
Eileen.

22:40.587 --> 22:43.322
I don't think we've met.

22:43.340 --> 22:46.092
Oh, Nick.
This is Jerry.

22:46.126 --> 22:48.010
Jerry, this is Nick.

22:48.045 --> 22:49.495
- And you are?
- Lindsey.

22:49.513 --> 22:51.397
Hi. Hello, Mrs. Rand.

22:51.431 --> 22:53.999
I mean, hello.

22:54.017 --> 22:55.601
We were just talking
about the show.

22:55.636 --> 22:58.104
- I don't like it much.
- Really?

22:58.138 --> 23:01.407
He's one of the most important
directors in the world.

23:01.441 --> 23:03.075
I wouldn't know
about that.

23:03.110 --> 23:07.046
Just think that art maybe should
be a little more entertaining.

23:07.080 --> 23:08.447
You're a populist.

23:08.482 --> 23:10.683
Is that a bad thing,
Jerry?

23:10.717 --> 23:12.918
Not if you're one
of the masses.

23:20.994 --> 23:23.028
Are you okay?

23:23.046 --> 23:25.381
- Yeah. Fine.
- Come on, Tom.

23:25.415 --> 23:27.633
You've been someplace else
all night.

23:27.668 --> 23:30.086
You hardly said three words
to poor Ivy.

23:30.137 --> 23:33.606
Leo's missing.

23:33.640 --> 23:35.941
Leo?

23:35.976 --> 23:39.078
Julia's son.
He's... missing.

23:39.112 --> 23:40.813
No one can know.

23:40.847 --> 23:42.948
She's... they're looking
for him.

23:42.983 --> 23:45.217
How long has he been gone?

23:45.252 --> 23:46.452
Three days.

23:46.486 --> 23:48.988
Wow.

23:49.022 --> 23:50.573
[Elevator dings]

23:50.607 --> 23:52.258
Very interesting,
your friend.

23:52.292 --> 23:54.827
Ugh, Jerry,
do we have to do this?

23:54.861 --> 23:57.496
I'm just surprised.

23:57.531 --> 24:00.533
It's a little late to start
dating the pool boy, isn't it?

24:03.303 --> 24:04.570
You know what?

24:04.604 --> 24:06.739
I'm bored too.
Let's go.

24:06.773 --> 24:09.508
A woman
after my own heart.

24:14.981 --> 24:17.600
He's cute.

24:17.634 --> 24:20.136
It's media.
You use them. It's a game.

24:20.187 --> 24:22.588
In my experience, the press
don't actually like to be used.

24:22.606 --> 24:24.440
[Chuckles]
What do you do?

24:24.474 --> 24:26.859
Dev works in the press office
for the mayor.

24:26.893 --> 24:28.794
Oh, that's right.
That's right. You told me.

24:28.829 --> 24:31.997
And you are, um...
How high up are you?

24:32.032 --> 24:34.033
How high up am I?

24:34.067 --> 24:35.468
Well, you know
what I'm saying, then.

24:35.502 --> 24:36.935
It's when you're
in front of them,

24:36.953 --> 24:38.604
and they're coming
after you...

24:38.622 --> 24:40.272
That's the moment
you have to try to control it.

24:40.307 --> 24:41.490
I mean, I like the press,
but...

24:41.541 --> 24:42.842
So you want them
to think

24:42.876 --> 24:44.109
that Karen is your lover.

24:44.127 --> 24:45.444
Do you want
some saag paneer?

24:45.462 --> 24:46.996
They said
there's no nuts in it.

24:47.047 --> 24:49.682
No. I just want her picture
in the newspaper.

24:49.716 --> 24:51.617
- I want her to be a star.
- Why?

24:51.651 --> 24:53.686
Because
that's what she wants.

24:53.720 --> 24:55.287
Maybe she should decide
what she wants.

24:55.322 --> 24:56.689
Maybe I should.

24:56.723 --> 24:59.325
Maybe you guys should stop talking
about me as if I weren't here.

24:59.359 --> 25:02.061
I told you
this would be a problem.

25:02.095 --> 25:03.529
- I'm sorry, what?
- Okay.

25:03.563 --> 25:05.397
Just hang on,
both of you guys.

25:05.432 --> 25:06.966
Your ego gets in the way,

25:07.000 --> 25:08.701
and, I mean,
you're losing control of her,

25:08.735 --> 25:10.169
and it's scary
and frustrating.

25:10.203 --> 25:11.654
I mean, I know.

25:11.688 --> 25:14.173
With respect,
I just met you 20 minutes ago.

25:14.207 --> 25:16.842
You're in no position to define my
relationship with my girlfriend.

25:16.877 --> 25:18.344
I'm just describing
what I see

25:18.378 --> 25:19.812
and what I know.

25:19.846 --> 25:21.547
So this is what
she's telling you while

25:21.581 --> 25:22.982
- you're running around New York?
- No.

25:23.016 --> 25:24.700
No, no, don't go
getting offended.

25:24.751 --> 25:26.085
Oh, and you're the expert.

25:26.119 --> 25:28.154
'Cause I hear
your boyfriend Colin

25:28.188 --> 25:29.388
had to be escorted from the room
using mace.

25:29.422 --> 25:30.673
I'm just trying to help.

25:30.707 --> 25:32.057
I think maybe
we should leave.

25:32.092 --> 25:33.592
I'm sure
you're a great guy.

25:33.627 --> 25:35.995
- I love her.
- You sound pretty defensive.

25:36.029 --> 25:38.197
"I love her"
is defensive?

25:38.231 --> 25:40.332
If you love her, you should
want what's best for her.

25:40.367 --> 25:42.017
♪ Darling, the hands of time ♪

25:42.052 --> 25:43.669
♪ Must always point ahead ♪

25:43.703 --> 25:45.104
♪ Yesterday's past ♪

25:45.138 --> 25:46.772
♪ Today has come and gone ♪

25:46.807 --> 25:49.208
♪ The secret of tomorrow's
coming fast ♪

25:49.242 --> 25:51.844
♪ Which bedtime story
shall I sing to you ♪

25:51.862 --> 25:53.846
♪ When we turn out
the lights ♪

25:53.880 --> 25:55.414
♪ One of eternity ♪

25:55.448 --> 25:58.016
♪ Or one of just a thousand
and one nights ♪

25:58.034 --> 25:59.418
♪ Is there a mystic ♪

25:59.452 --> 26:03.205
♪ With the answers
from above ♪

26:03.240 --> 26:04.790
♪ Is there a goddess ♪

26:04.825 --> 26:06.959
♪ With the hourglass
of love ♪

26:06.993 --> 26:09.094
♪ So many questions ♪

26:09.129 --> 26:11.130
♪ Swirling all around
my heart ♪

26:11.164 --> 26:12.898
♪ Is this the end ♪

26:12.933 --> 26:14.700
♪ Or just the start ♪

26:14.718 --> 26:16.802
♪ Will I shower you
with riches ♪

26:16.837 --> 26:18.971
♪ Every year
the night we met ♪

26:19.005 --> 26:21.590
♪ Will you take my heart
or melt it ♪

26:21.641 --> 26:22.875
♪ Like it's gold ♪

26:22.909 --> 26:25.211
♪ Will our love
go on forever ♪

26:25.245 --> 26:27.546
♪ Or is this
all that we get ♪

26:27.581 --> 26:28.948
♪ Is tonight the last ♪

26:28.982 --> 26:31.450
♪ Or does the future hold ♪

26:31.484 --> 26:35.254
♪ A lifetime of delights ♪

26:35.288 --> 26:39.258
♪ Or just a thousand
and one nights ♪

26:39.292 --> 26:41.961
[Vocalizing]

26:41.995 --> 26:46.265
♪ ♪

26:46.299 --> 26:47.900
♪ Darling, you seem to think ♪

26:47.934 --> 26:50.169
♪ That I'm the only one
who has to choose ♪

26:50.203 --> 26:51.770
♪ That you are in control ♪

26:51.805 --> 26:54.423
♪ And get to set the rules
of win or lose ♪

26:54.457 --> 26:57.276
♪ The bedtime story
that I'll sing to you ♪

26:57.310 --> 26:58.978
♪ When we turn out
the lights ♪

26:59.012 --> 27:01.247
♪ Might bring eternity ♪

27:01.281 --> 27:03.849
♪ Or maybe just a thousand
and one nights ♪

27:03.884 --> 27:07.953
♪ There is no mystic
with the answers from above ♪

27:07.988 --> 27:09.355
♪ You know the secrets ♪

27:09.389 --> 27:12.257
♪ For the way
to keep my love ♪

27:12.275 --> 27:15.194
♪ There are a thousand
and more ways ♪

27:15.228 --> 27:16.962
♪ To win my heart ♪

27:16.997 --> 27:20.332
♪ The list is long
but for a start ♪

27:20.367 --> 27:22.001
♪ You can shower me
with riches ♪

27:22.035 --> 27:24.320
♪ Every year
the night we met ♪

27:24.371 --> 27:26.205
♪ I may take your heart
and melt it ♪

27:26.239 --> 27:27.840
♪ Like it's gold ♪

27:27.874 --> 27:30.943
♪ Stray in someone's
perfumed garden ♪

27:30.961 --> 27:33.145
♪ And this night's
the last you'll get ♪

27:33.179 --> 27:36.782
♪ Play your cards right
and the future just might hold ♪

27:36.800 --> 27:40.669
♪ A lifetime of delights ♪

27:40.720 --> 27:46.058
♪ Or just a thousand
and one nights ♪

27:46.092 --> 27:49.295
[Vocalizing]

27:49.329 --> 27:54.700
♪ Just a thousand
and one nights ♪

27:54.734 --> 27:56.869
♪ The man who never chooses ♪

27:56.903 --> 27:59.822
♪ Finds himself
without a choice ♪

27:59.856 --> 28:04.243
♪ The lucky ones
appear to have it all ♪

28:04.277 --> 28:05.711
♪ The tiger's just a kitten ♪

28:05.745 --> 28:08.514
♪ When his tamer
finds her voice ♪

28:08.548 --> 28:11.850
♪ I surely will obey you
when you call ♪

28:11.885 --> 28:14.336
♪ Then will you
shower me with riches ♪

28:14.371 --> 28:16.422
♪ Every year
the night we met ♪

28:16.456 --> 28:20.259
♪ Will you take my heart
and melt it like it's gold ♪

28:20.293 --> 28:23.195
♪ Will our love
go on forever ♪

28:23.229 --> 28:25.431
♪ Or is this
all that we get ♪

28:25.465 --> 28:29.201
♪ Is tonight the last
or does the future hold ♪

28:29.235 --> 28:31.503
♪ A lifetime of delights ♪

28:31.521 --> 28:33.005
♪ A lifetime of delights ♪

28:33.039 --> 28:36.208
♪ Or just a thousand
and one nights ♪

28:36.242 --> 28:38.410
[Vocalizing]

28:38.445 --> 28:41.780
♪ ♪

28:41.815 --> 28:45.217
♪ Just a thousand
and one nights ♪

28:45.251 --> 28:48.220
[Vocalizing]

28:48.254 --> 28:51.457
♪ ♪

29:11.589 --> 29:13.223
Whales.

29:13.257 --> 29:15.458
Smartest animal
on the planet.

29:15.460 --> 29:18.461
Smarter than us, certainly.

29:24.135 --> 29:26.369
- Keith Richards.
- Mm-hmm.

29:26.404 --> 29:28.872
I always wanted to be
Keith Richards.

29:28.906 --> 29:33.410
That makes the whales
a whole lot smarter than you.

29:33.444 --> 29:37.380
Maybe, maybe not.

29:37.415 --> 29:40.417
You look pretty
with your hair like that.

29:43.254 --> 29:45.238
What?

29:48.626 --> 29:50.927
It's just...

29:50.962 --> 29:54.664
You're so different
from Jerry.

29:54.699 --> 29:56.233
There, I've said it.

29:56.267 --> 30:00.103
But you're just so different
from Jerry.

30:00.137 --> 30:03.740
Yeah. What was that
all about?

30:03.774 --> 30:06.943
Well, he's angry
that I finally left him,

30:06.978 --> 30:10.814
and he doesn't mind
letting me know.

30:10.848 --> 30:12.515
No, I mean,
why did you love him?

30:12.550 --> 30:16.086
That mean streak,
that's not a new thing, is it?

30:16.120 --> 30:18.021
Well, I guess
when you're young,

30:18.055 --> 30:20.357
you think that's strong,

30:20.391 --> 30:23.593
and you think that strength
will protect you.

30:23.628 --> 30:26.630
You don't think
it'll turn against you.

30:30.067 --> 30:33.069
Well, you're trading up.

30:45.349 --> 30:51.054
[Indistinct chatter]

30:51.088 --> 30:53.340
You better talk to me
right now, you little creep,

30:53.391 --> 30:55.859
or I'm gonna make your life
a living hell.

30:55.893 --> 30:58.328
- Look, I don't know anything.
- I'm famous.

30:58.362 --> 30:59.980
I've had plays on Broadway.

31:00.014 --> 31:01.765
That sort of thing
means something

31:01.799 --> 31:04.367
to people in private schools
in New York City.

31:04.402 --> 31:07.837
If I tell your principal
that you got Leo hooked on drugs

31:07.872 --> 31:09.306
and helped him run away,

31:09.340 --> 31:12.242
you're gonna have
a lot to answer for.

31:12.276 --> 31:14.911
Okay. Sure.
You can make all that happen.

31:14.946 --> 31:17.647
You're all hooked up.
So what?

31:17.665 --> 31:19.215
You screwed up your life
so bad,

31:19.250 --> 31:20.650
you have to run around,
like,

31:20.668 --> 31:23.687
threatening loser teenagers.

31:25.790 --> 31:29.592
Where is he?

31:29.627 --> 31:31.227
Sleeping on the floor
of my room.

31:31.262 --> 31:34.197
He just needed some space,

31:34.231 --> 31:37.233
'cause his parents
were driving him so nuts.

31:43.391 --> 31:44.891
Is he all right?

31:44.942 --> 31:46.359
[Scoffs]
If he was all right,

31:46.394 --> 31:48.578
do you think
he would've done this?

31:48.612 --> 31:49.846
You know what,
let me tell you something

31:49.880 --> 31:51.231
before you freak out again.

31:51.282 --> 31:53.283
This isn't his fault.

31:53.317 --> 31:57.537
It's not my fault either.

31:57.571 --> 31:59.089
No, it's not.

31:59.123 --> 32:02.959
Look, I'll tell him
to call you.

32:02.994 --> 32:05.829
I don't know if he will.

32:09.133 --> 32:12.886
We're starting
with act two, please.

32:12.920 --> 32:16.106
No Julia. Again.

32:16.140 --> 32:18.875
She's under the weather.

32:18.909 --> 32:20.610
Flu or something.

32:23.314 --> 32:26.783
I'm gonna kill him.
Leo, not Mason.

32:26.817 --> 32:28.451
I'm gonna kill 'em both,
and I'm gonna kill

32:28.486 --> 32:30.437
- that know-nothing mother.
- Frank, Frank, honey.

32:30.488 --> 32:31.988
It's okay. It's okay.
You don't need to...

32:32.023 --> 32:33.323
Don't tell me
what to do.

32:33.357 --> 32:34.607
Okay. Okay, Frank.

32:34.658 --> 32:36.559
But you know what?

32:36.594 --> 32:38.461
You are always
so good in a crisis,

32:38.496 --> 32:42.632
and you hold everything in
so that I can lose it.

32:42.666 --> 32:45.001
And then, after everything
is better, you lose it.

32:45.036 --> 32:47.003
But that's the thing.
You don't have to.

32:47.038 --> 32:50.306
He's okay.

32:54.295 --> 32:56.780
You don't think
I should go get him?

32:56.814 --> 33:00.016
He just needs
a little room.

33:06.490 --> 33:09.526
I was so scared.

33:11.228 --> 33:13.980
I know.

33:18.903 --> 33:21.704
Ellis, would you make
another smoothie?

33:21.739 --> 33:23.156
You want one?
They're awesome.

33:23.207 --> 33:24.624
- Sure.
- I'll be right back.

33:24.658 --> 33:26.326
I'm gonna go get some chips.

33:26.377 --> 33:28.144
It's a really short break.
You want me to go?

33:28.179 --> 33:29.946
Oh, no, I'll do it.
I gotta get the right ones.

33:29.964 --> 33:32.782
No peanut oil.

33:32.817 --> 33:34.684
[Sighs]

33:34.718 --> 33:36.553
It's like some
demented fairy tale.

33:36.587 --> 33:39.689
You drink a magic potion,
you kiss a movie star,

33:39.723 --> 33:43.560
and presto,
you're one too.

33:43.594 --> 33:45.862
Are they really that awesome?

33:45.896 --> 33:48.031
They are all
she drinks and eats.

33:48.065 --> 33:49.332
And potato chips.

33:49.366 --> 33:51.901
And potato chips.

33:51.936 --> 33:54.003
- Ellis?
- Hm?

33:54.038 --> 33:56.172
Would you do something
for me?

33:56.207 --> 33:58.641
For you, anything.

33:58.676 --> 34:00.410
Don't you want to know
what it is first?

34:00.444 --> 34:03.446
Hit me.
I'll do it.

34:08.214 --> 34:11.514
Hey. Can I borrow your phone?

34:14.650 --> 34:16.449
Thanks.

34:16.467 --> 34:17.668
Are we back?

34:17.719 --> 34:20.054
Rebecca's not here.

34:20.088 --> 34:22.123
- Where is she?
- Oh, she went out.

34:22.157 --> 34:23.556
Went out why?

34:23.592 --> 34:26.594
Potato chips.
I think she needs special ones.

34:31.500 --> 34:34.685
Special potato chips.

34:34.735 --> 34:37.071
Terrific.

34:37.105 --> 34:38.873
We should get
to your song today.

34:38.907 --> 34:41.742
Oh. No, we're not.

34:41.777 --> 34:43.527
Julia has the flu.
I'm done for the day.

34:43.578 --> 34:46.030
Oh, okay.
See you later. Bye.

34:46.081 --> 34:48.049
Ms. Duvall,
can I have your autograph?

34:48.083 --> 34:49.550
Sure.

34:52.888 --> 34:54.088
Hey.

34:54.121 --> 34:56.357
Oh, I'm sorry.

34:56.391 --> 34:59.326
You are 15 minutes late
from a 10-minute break.

34:59.344 --> 35:01.328
- Derek, calm down.
- Don't tell me to calm do...

35:01.346 --> 35:02.763
You get that bloody thing
out of my face.

35:02.798 --> 35:04.098
Hey, hey!

35:04.132 --> 35:05.766
I could have you arrested
for that!

35:05.801 --> 35:07.935
Yeah, good luck with that.
Let's go.

35:07.969 --> 35:09.720
- I want them gone.
- I don't tell them...

35:09.771 --> 35:12.440
Oh, just call your publicist
and get rid of them.

35:12.474 --> 35:14.608
And get your ass
to my rehearsals on time,

35:14.643 --> 35:15.943
and stop messing about
with your understudy.

35:15.977 --> 35:18.045
In fact, stop messing about
with me.

35:18.080 --> 35:19.447
This show
is going to Broadway,

35:19.481 --> 35:21.182
where it's going to be
a blinding hit.

35:21.216 --> 35:23.751
I am not about to let
some stupid little movie star

35:23.785 --> 35:27.204
with childish power issues
stop it... or me.

35:27.239 --> 35:30.891
Okay.

35:30.926 --> 35:32.259
Chip?

35:32.294 --> 35:34.028
No.

35:34.062 --> 35:37.898
Right. Having lost 20 minutes
to miss Duvall's need

35:37.933 --> 35:39.633
for her oh-so-special
potato chips,

35:39.668 --> 35:41.769
we are now finally
in a position to start

35:41.803 --> 35:43.404
<i>Secondhand</i>
<i>white baby grand,</i>

35:43.438 --> 35:44.905
marking the transition
into <i>dig deep.</i>

35:44.940 --> 35:48.559
Karen Cartwright.

35:48.593 --> 35:49.944
Where is Karen Cartwright?!

35:49.978 --> 35:52.113
- She went home.
- Terrific.

35:52.147 --> 35:55.583
- She got a text...
- Be quiet!

35:55.617 --> 35:59.920
Ivy. Do you know it?

35:59.955 --> 36:02.656
Yes. Yes, I do.

36:02.691 --> 36:03.941
Great, it's yours.

36:03.992 --> 36:05.326
You okay with that, Tom?

36:05.360 --> 36:07.394
- Yes, I am.
- Fine.

36:07.412 --> 36:09.113
Marilyn,
you're center stage.

36:09.164 --> 36:12.433
Ivy, you're in the shadowbox
upstage center right.

36:12.467 --> 36:15.453
<i>Now!</i>

36:24.012 --> 36:26.147
Hey.

36:26.181 --> 36:29.183
- Hey.
- Hey.

36:32.521 --> 36:34.588
I'm sorry.

36:34.623 --> 36:36.457
I shouldn't have done that.

36:36.491 --> 36:40.795
I couldn't stand...

36:40.829 --> 36:42.963
I know you kept saying
it wasn't my fault,

36:42.998 --> 36:45.266
but I felt like I was
losing everything,

36:45.300 --> 36:46.500
and I didn't know why.

36:46.535 --> 36:47.785
You're not losing...

36:47.819 --> 36:49.170
Dad, come on.

36:49.204 --> 36:51.839
I am.
We are.

36:55.977 --> 36:58.979
I don't know
what anything is any more.

37:03.819 --> 37:07.621
Dinner will make us all
feel better.

37:07.656 --> 37:09.523
Will it?

37:09.558 --> 37:14.061
Yes, it will.

37:14.095 --> 37:17.097
Go set the table.

37:23.655 --> 37:25.840
You okay?

37:25.874 --> 37:27.074
Tom, you okay?

37:27.108 --> 37:29.994
[Exhales heavily]

37:30.028 --> 37:32.246
He's back.
He came back.

37:32.280 --> 37:33.914
That is really
wonderful news.

37:33.949 --> 37:35.249
He's back.
He's fine. He's back.

37:35.283 --> 37:37.718
- Yeah, he's back!
- [Laughing]

37:37.752 --> 37:40.354
So...

37:40.388 --> 37:43.524
The idea is, uh,
I lie here

37:43.558 --> 37:46.160
and listen to her sing.

37:46.194 --> 37:47.895
She's a voice in your head.

37:47.929 --> 37:51.265
Okay.

37:53.268 --> 37:55.553
Okay, go ahead.

37:55.604 --> 37:59.440
Remember. Remember.

37:59.474 --> 38:01.609
[Imitating Marilyn]
Is that all I have to do?

38:01.643 --> 38:04.879
That's all you have to do,
my dear Marilyn.

38:04.913 --> 38:08.349
Look within.

38:08.383 --> 38:11.418
It's who you are
in your deepest soul

38:11.453 --> 38:13.954
that will make you
a great actress.

38:13.989 --> 38:15.556
A great actress.

38:15.590 --> 38:18.058
A great actress.

38:18.093 --> 38:20.060
Hmm. Hmm.

38:20.095 --> 38:22.863
Remember your youth.

38:22.898 --> 38:24.565
Mama bought the piano.

38:24.599 --> 38:26.767
Remember your childhood.

38:26.801 --> 38:29.403
Then mama went away.

